ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Is a cheerful child.
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Exhibits wide mood swings (child's emotional
state difficult to anticipate because he/she moves
quickly from a positive to a negative mood).
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Responds positively to neutral or friendly
overtures by adults. [responds positively to polite or
friendly adults]
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Transitions well from one activity to another;
doesn't become angry, anxious, distressed, or
overly excited when moving from one activity to
another.
Notes: 1= Almost Always; 2= Often; 3= Sometimes; 4= Rarely/ Never; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Can recover quickly from upset or distress (for
example, doesn't pout or remain sullen, anxious, or
sad after emotionally distressing events).
Notes: 1= Almost Always; 2= Often; 3= Sometimes; 4= Rarely/ Never; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Is easily frustrated.
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Responds positively neutral or friendly
overtures by peers. [Responds positively to polite or
friendly peers.]
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Is prone to angry outbursts/ tantrums easily.
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Is able to delay gratification.
Notes: 1= Almost Always; 2= Often; 3= Sometimes; 4= Rarely/ Never; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Takes pleasure in the distress of other (for
example, laughs when another person gets hurt or
punished; seems to enjoy teasing others).
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Can modulate excitement [Can control his/her
excitement] (for example, doesn't get carried
away in high-energy play situations or overly
excited in inappropriate contexts).
Notes: 1= Almost Always; 2= Often; 3= Sometimes; 4= Rarely/ Never; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Is whiny or clingy with adults.
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Is prone to have disruptive outbursts of energy

Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Responds angrily to limit-setting by adults.
Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:
Can say when s/he is feeling sad, angry, or mad,

Notes: 1= Rarely/ Never; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Almost Always; -1= Unanswered questions; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription: Seems sad or listless.
Notes: 1= Almost Always; 2= Often; 3= Sometimes; 4= Rarely/ Never; -7= Skipped or left unanswered; -8= I don't know the answer to the question; -9= I don't want to answer the question

ElementDescription:

ElementDescription:

ElementDescription:
Responds negatively to neutral or friendly

ElementDescription: Is impulsive [Can't control him/herself].

ElementDescription:
Is empathic [sympathetic] towards others; show

ElementDescription:
Displays exuberance [energy and excitement]

ElementDescription:
Displays appropriate negative emotions (anger,

ElementDescription:
Displays negative emotions when attempting to
